      "metadata": {
        "id": "q-xZp3ny8WOJ"
      },
      "source": [
        "###Exercise: Discussion about Determining Light Curve Period\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   From this plot, does it look like there is an exoplanet circling this star with a regular period?\n",
        "2.   Approximately what do you think the period of this exoplanet is? (Each time step is about 30 minutes.)\n",
        "3.   Looking at the plot, do you think the telescope started measuring the brightness of the star at the start, middle, or end of one period?\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pffFCNpS9yc7"
      },
      "source": [
        "###Exercise: Plotting One Period of the Exoplanet Orbit\n",
        "\n",
        "To recognize exoplanets, we need to get comfortable finding the period from a graph!\n",
        "\n",
        "Here, we want to try to visualize one period of the exoplanet transit (starting at a dip and ending at a dip). Let's see if we can find the time `t_0`, the time at which the first transit (dip in plot) starts. Then, we will see if we can find the period length (time from dip to dip), so we can plot one period from start to finish.\n",
        "\n",
        "*Hint:* to begin, set the period to 3197 to first figure out `t_0`. Then, reset the period."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "cellView": "form",
        "id": "SeKZQHI56OJ8",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 887
        },
        "outputId": "689aee2f-f782-4b63-a411-8b2a54f64862"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "index = 0 #@param {type:\"slider\", min:0, max:37, step:1}\n",
        "t_0 = 1568 #@param {type:\"slider\", min:0, max:3197, step:1}\n",
        "period = 802 #@param {type:\"slider\", min:0, max:3197, step:1}\n",
        "\n",
        "from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle\n",
        "light_curve=np.array(exo_data.loc[index])\n",
        "plt.plot(light_curve)\n",
        "plt.title('Box Covering One Period of Exoplanet Transit')\n",
        "plt.gca().add_patch(Rectangle((t_0, -510), period, 700, linewidth=1,edgecolor='r',facecolor='none'))\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(light_curve[t_0: t_0+period])\n",
        "plt.title('Plot of Just One Period')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kSHk0nrZ_u2P"
      },
      "source": [
        "###Exercise: Folding Light Curves\n",
        "\n",
        "Now, let's try to manually determine if something is an exoplanet! You want to check: is the period the same for all of the dips?\n",
        "\n",
        "The method used to check this is known as **folding**. Folding means plotting all of the periods on top of each other to see if there is a consistent trend.\n",
        "\n",
        "*Note:* there is a lot of noise in this data, so each period will not be quite identical. Most importantly, we want to check if the dips occur at roughly the same places.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Below, set the time at which period 1 starts as `start_period_1` and the time at which period 2 starts as `start_period_2`, using your variables `t_0` and `period` from before. Then plot two versions of the curve: starting from the first period and starting from the second period!\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zQDQd9yUC5Hn",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 448
        },
        "outputId": "6a2ecf4d-4476-4ad2-93d3-e94b791b0a11"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7cca7beed110>]"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 93
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "#Plot the curve starting from Period 1\n",
        "start_period_1 = t_0 ### YOUR CODE HERE - time of first transit\n",
        "plt.plot(light_curve[start_period_1:(start_period_1+period)]) #plots the first curve\n",
        "\n",
        "#Plot the curve starting from Period 2\n",
        "start_period_2 = t_0 + period\n",
        "plt.plot(light_curve[start_period_2:(start_period_2+period)])\n",
        "### YOUR CODE HERE"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
